<subSubSection id="C34CD692D11E497E79C3C0DEFCE0359B" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C0DEFEBF35CD" blockId="7.[189,324,401,427]" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<heading id="D0A13275D11E497E79C3C0DEFEBF35CD" bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E79C3C0DEFEBF35CD" bold="true" box="[189,324,401,427]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C0F0FCE0359B" blockId="7.[189,1398,447,509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
The specific epithet is to be treated as an adjective and is composed of ‘ 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E7D5EC0F0FB9E35BF" box="[1056,1125,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">brevi-</emphasis>
’, meaning ‘short’, and ‘- 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E79AFC0ACFEDA359A" box="[209,289,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">scapus</emphasis>
’, a reference to the small size of the scape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D11E497E79C3C36BFBC536BB" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C36BFE973658" blockId="7.[189,364,548,574]" box="[189,364,548,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
