<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E79C3C36BFE973658" bold="true" box="[189,364,548,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Type material</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C31DFD3F360A" blockId="7.[189,708,594,621]" box="[189,708,594,621]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<materialsCitation id="3B3E8F44D11E497E79C3C31DFD3F360A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3753601303" box="[189,708,594,621]" collectionCode="NHMD" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" specimenCode="NHMD-300622" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-male="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="54ED3BBBD11E497E79C3C31DFED1360A" box="[189,298,594,620]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCode id="DBF02D62D11E497E784FC31DFE14360A" box="[305,495,594,620]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">NHMD-300622</specimenCode>
, a complete 
<specimenCount id="9D504E90D11E497E7BFDC31DFD3B360A" box="[643,704,594,620]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" type="male">male</specimenCount>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C3DBFE3936C8" blockId="7.[189,450,660,686]" box="[189,450,660,686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<heading id="D0A13275D11E497E79C3C3DBFE3936C8" bold="true" box="[189,450,660,686]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E79C3C3DBFE3936C8" bold="true" box="[189,450,660,686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Locality and horizon</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C38DFBC536BB" blockId="7.[189,1086,706,733]" box="[189,1086,706,733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Baltic amber is considered to be of Bartonian–Priabonian age, ca 34–38 Ma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D11E497E79C3C24BFEC23371" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C24BFEB53778" blockId="7.[189,334,772,798]" box="[189,334,772,798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<heading id="D0A13275D11E497E79C3C24BFEB53778" bold="true" box="[189,334,772,798]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E79C3C24BFEB53778" bold="true" box="[189,334,772,798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E7994C27CFED1372B" blockId="7.[189,1406,819,1091]" box="[234,298,819,845]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E7994C27CFED1372B" bold="true" box="[234,298,819,845]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C219FD8C3025" blockId="7.[189,1406,819,1091]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
BODY. BL 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E783EC219FEAA3716" bold="true" box="[320,337,854,880]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">=</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E7825C219FE313716" box="[347,458,854,880]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.61" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="3.61">3.61 mm</quantity>
. Head with sparse long hairs (HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E7AE9C219FBF33716" box="[919,1032,854,880]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.699999999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.47">0.47 mm</quantity>
); eye oval, glabrous; antennae inserted on transverse shelf; 14 antennomeres with uniform pilosity; scape elongate, less than five times as long as wide; pedicel rounded, as long as wide; flagellomeres elongate, cylindrical; F1 1.2 times as long as scape, with a deep emargination covering almost half of segment; F2–F6 slightly shorter, of subequal length; F6–F12 decreasing in size but still much more longer than wide; F12 tapering at apex (antennomeres length, in mm, when possible: Sc-0.32; P-0.06; F1-0.39; F2-0.34; F3-0.32); mandibles of ordinary form, not forming a beak.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C524FE0C3182" blockId="7.[187,1400,1130,1508]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
MESOSOMA. Shorter than metasoma (MsL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E7BC0C525FCD030E3" box="[702,811,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.21" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="1.21">1.21 mm</quantity>
); pronotum without epomia, only visible in lateral view; mesoscutum smooth; notauli deep, diverging at posterior terminations toward a point outside scutellum; anterior scutellar pit bean-shaped; scutellum without posterior scutellar pits; mesopleuron with epicnemial pit, epicnemial bridge and subalar bridge present; propodeum with prominent plicae; median propodeal keel simple. Fore wing hyaline, uniformly micropubescent (FwL= 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E7DEAC5B8FAFB3174" box="[1172,1280,1271,1298]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.58" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="3.58">3.58 mm</quantity>
); venation complete with C, Sc+R, basal vein, M+Cu, marginal vein, r-rs and Rs pigmented; marginal vein very long, longer than its distance from basal vein and as long as radial cell; postmarginal vein fading after middle of radial cell; Rs proximally directed toward base of wing; M inconspicuous towards apex; Cu short and nebulous; radial cell closed. Hind wing narrow, with C pigmented and basal cell opened (HwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E7861C4E8FE7731A4" box="[287,396,1447,1474]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.23" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.23">2.23 mm</quantity>
). Legs slender, covered with setae; tibial spur formula 1-2-2; hind tibia and tarsomeres with long recumbent hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C743FB3B32D4" blockId="7.[189,1401,1548,1715]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
METASOMA. Petiole elongate, almost three times as long as its middle height (PtL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E7DD2C743FAE13240" box="[1196,1306,1548,1575]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.56">0.56 mm</quantity>
; PtW = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E79C1C760FED5322F" box="[191,302,1583,1609]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.19">0.19 mm</quantity>
), with longitudinal ribs; gaster globose, oval, smooth (GL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E7D7BC760FB88322F" box="[1029,1139,1583,1609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.37" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="1.37">1.37 mm</quantity>
; GH = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11E497E7DB1C760FAC5322F" box="[1231,1342,1583,1609]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.71">0.71 mm</quantity>
); six segments identifiable; T2 longest, covering two thirds of gaster; other tergites reduced, decreasing in length until they become indistinguishable; S2 longest, longer than T2; following sternites very short; pygidium and hypopygium at least as long as previous segments; genitalia internalized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E7994C795FEBE3292" blockId="7.[189,325,1754,1815]" box="[234,325,1754,1780]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E7994C795FEBE3292" bold="true" box="[234,325,1754,1780]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C7B2FEC23371" blockId="7.[189,325,1754,1815]" box="[189,313,1789,1815]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D11E497079C3C671FAEB3590" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497E79C3C671FEBF333E" blockId="7.[189,324,1854,1880]" box="[189,324,1854,1880]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<heading id="D0A13275D11E497E79C3C671FEBF333E" bold="true" box="[189,324,1854,1880]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E79C3C671FEBF333E" bold="true" box="[189,324,1854,1880]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11E497079C3C622FAEB3590" blockId="7.[189,1401,1901,1998]" lastBlockId="9.[188,1400,265,503]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
Using 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11E497E7873C622FE3833EE" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[269,451,1901,1928]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
key, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11E497E7B78C621FD0E33E1" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[518,757,1901,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E7B78C621FD0E33E1" box="[518,757,1901,1928]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Cinetus breviscapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11E497E7B81C621FCA733EE" box="[767,860,1902,1928]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out to 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11E497E7A88C621FB1633E1" authority="Jurine, 1807" authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[1014,1261,1901,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11E497E7A88C621FBAB33EE" box="[1014,1104,1902,1928]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Cinetus</emphasis>
Jurine, 1807
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: mandibles of ordinary form, scutellum without a row of foveae posteriorly, marginal vein very long, notauli slightly divergent posteriorly. Following 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11E497E7D51C6FCFB1F33A8" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[1071,1252,1971,1998]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
key to male species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11149717840C046FE6D3545" authorityName="Jurine" authorityYear="1807" box="[318,406,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11149717840C046FE6D3545" box="[318,406,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="65">Cinetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD111497178D8C046FD6F3545" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[422,660,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD111497178D8C046FD6F3545" box="[422,660,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="65">Cinetus breviscapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys out near 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11149717A39C046FBB73542" authority="Nixon, 1957" authorityName="Nixon" authorityYear="1957" box="[839,1100,265,292]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aletes">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11149717A39C046FC543545" box="[839,943,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="65">C. aletes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11149717AC9C046FBB73542" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[951,1100,265,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because of its scape that is shorter than F1 but differs in having the first flagellomere less distinctly longer than the scape (ratio scape length/F1 length: 1.2 vs 1.43; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11149717B09C000FCF2350C" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[631,777,335,362]" pageId="8" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon 1957</bibRefCitation>
), the petiole longer (three times as long as wide vs “about two and a half times as long as wide”) and being bigger (body length ca 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11149717D1AC03DFB4535EB" box="[1124,1214,370,397]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
vs ca 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11149717C76C03CFA9C35EB" box="[1288,1383,371,397]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
). In Baltic amber, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD110497078FFC046FD963545" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[385,621,265,291]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD110497078FFC046FD963545" box="[385,621,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Cinetus breviscapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11049707B0BC045FD2B3542" box="[629,720,266,292]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is considered as separate from 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11049707D3EC046FF033520" authority="Maneval, 1938" authorityName="Maneval" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inclusus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11049707D3EC046FAFA3545" box="[1088,1281,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Cinetus inclusus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11049707C76C046FF033520" author="Maneval H." pageId="9" pageNumber="66" pagination="107 - 116" refId="ref15502" refString="Maneval H. 1938. Trois serphoides de l'ambre de la Baltique. Revue francaise d'Entomologie 5 (2): 107 - 116." type="journal article" year="1938">Maneval, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD1104970784FC062FCF83520" authority="Szabo &amp; Oehlke, 1986" authorityName="Szabo &amp; Oehlke" authorityYear="1986" box="[305,771,300,327]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balticus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD1104970784FC062FE0B3520" box="[305,496,300,327]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Cinetus balticus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11049707889C063FCF83520" author="Szabo J. B. &amp; Oehlke J." box="[503,771,300,326]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" pagination="99 - 106" refId="ref16664" refString="Szabo J. B. &amp; Oehlke J. 1986. Neue Proctotrupoidea aus dem Baltischen Bernstein. Beitrage zur Entomologie 36: 99 - 106." type="journal article" year="1986">Szabó &amp; Oehlke, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because it clearly does not fit with their descriptions. The petiole of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11049707819C01FFE1D350F" authorityName="Szabo &amp; Oehlke" authorityYear="1986" box="[359,486,335,362]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balticus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11049707819C01FFE1D350F" box="[359,486,335,362]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">C. balticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is longer than that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11049707B9AC01FFC6A350F" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[740,913,335,362]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11049707B9AC01FFC6A350F" box="[740,913,335,362]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">C. breviscapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ratio length/middle height: 4 vs 2.8) and the fore wing venation is different (
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11049707B1AC03CFCE935EA" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[612,786,370,397]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11049707B1AC03CFCE935EA" box="[612,786,370,397]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">C. breviscapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a longer marginal vein, a longer radial cell, the postmarginal vein does not extend beyond the radial cell and Rs is conspicuous for almost all its length). 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD110497079C2C0F6FE8635B5" authorityName="Maneval" authorityYear="1938" box="[188,381,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inclusus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD110497079C2C0F6FE8635B5" box="[188,381,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Cinetus inclusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a shorter petiole (ratio length/middle height: 1.5) and the scape as long as pedicel, F1 and half of F2 combined, unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11049707B1DC092FCEB3590" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[611,784,476,503]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11049707B1DC092FCEB3590" box="[611,784,476,503]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">C. breviscapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whose scape is shorter than flagellomere 1.
</paragraph>
